{
  "texts": [
    "In dense tree (t=256) most of the runtime is bounded to near-field computation totally makes it slower than the base tree because the threads workload increases due to number of neighbours, i.e., each thread processes 16 times larger set of neighbours.",
    "The share of Near-Field operator was shown in Figure [6] too.",
    "Figure [3] and Table [1] show the relationship between tree density and runtime components.",
    "The left plot shows that near-field runtime increases with t, as larger interaction patterns require more computation.",
    "The middle plot shows the inverse behavior for far-field, which benefits from coarser boxes."
  ]
}